The only known distributional data are those mentioned by Berg for Buenos Aires province (Chacabuco and Almirante Brown departments) and some localities in Corrientes province (
Coscarón, 2003
;
Melo et al. , 2004
); consequently, the new records of this species in the provinces of Chaco, Entre Ríos, Misiones, Salta, and Santa Fe considerably extend its geographic distribution.

